Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_clock_exclusivity(25.10)                      set_clock_exclusivity(25.10)

Name
       set_clock_exclusivity - Controls filtering of mutually-exclusive clocks
       at strategic points in the design, e.g., the output of clock multiplex-
       ers

Syntax
       set_clock_exclusivity

       [-help]

       [-exclude_opposite_polarity]

       [-exclude_related_input_pins]

       [-exclude_same_polarity]

       [-group <clock_list>]

       [-inputs <<string>>]

       <pin_name>

       Controls  filtering of mutually-exclusive clocks at strategic points in
       the design, e.g., the output of clock multiplexers.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -exclude_opposite_polarity
              Isolates positive and negative phases of the clocks in the  same
              group.  By  default,  the  positive  and  negative phases of the
              clocks in the same group that arrive at a strategic  point  will
              not be isolated from each other.

       -exclude_related_input_pins
              Allows comparison of clocks going through the same input pins of
              the specified gate.

       -exclude_same_polarity
              Allows  comparison  of  clocks  going through the same launch or
              capture paths.

       -group <clock_list>
              Defines a set of clocks that are exclusive to the clocks defined
              in all other groups.

       -inputs <<string>>
              Specifies a list or collection of input pins for which clock ex-
              clusivity is to be recognized.

       <pin_name>
              Specifies the name of the pin.

Examples
              * The following command will cause downstream analysis from  the
                mux to isolate interactions between the groups:

                set_clock_exclusivity  -group  {CLK1  CLK2} -group {CLK3 CLK4}
                U1/Y

                This assertion will cause downstream analysis from pin U1/Y to
                isolate interactions between  the  groups.  The  groups  {CLK1
                CLK2}  and {CLK3 CLK4} are allowed, but all other combinations
                are considered logically exclusive.

Related Information
              * reset_clock_gating_check

              * create_clock

